It is estimated that the period 2009-2010 will be critical to continue the phase out of ODS consumption in Georgia, especially in order to facilitate implementation of the CFC 100% reduction measure of the Montreal Protocol. Approval of the extension of the Institutional Strengthening is essential to guarantee the success of the actions being proposed in the TPMP and other activities. In addition, the National Ozone Office will need to initiate actions related to the new decisions taken at MOP-19 pertaining to the HCFCs.
The new phase of the project shall focus planned activities on the following areas:
• Awareness raising campaigns to increase consciousness of decision-makers and population on ozone-related issues;
• Implementation, monitoring and coordination of the IS programme and all other related activities under the Montreal Protocol;
• Knowledge building and sharing on best practices in refrigeration,  Methyl Bromide and MDI sectors;
• Collection of information on ODS consumption and reporting to MFS and Ozone Secretariat.

